up items are noted but do not block merging.","comments":"## Part 1 — Spec Review\n\nAll five acceptance criteria from issue #52 are met:\n\n| AC | Requirement | Status |\n|---|---|---|\n| AC1 | Field-aware `.result` recovery for `pr_number`, `branch`, `tasks` | ✅ Implemented in `run_stage` fallback block |\n| AC2 | `gh pr list --head <branch>` fallback when `find-mr.sh` fails | ✅ Nested fallback added at PR creation section |\n| AC3 | Graduated retry: `_next_model_up` on task retry attempt 2+ | ✅ Implemented in implement-task loop |\n| AC4 | 20% timeout increase on `run_stage` retry after exit 124 | ✅ `retry_timeout=$(( stage_timeout + stage_timeout / 5 ))` |\n| AC5 | New BATS tests covering all recovery logic | ✅ +411 lines of tests |\n\nNo scope creep detected. All changes are tightly scoped to the four failure modes identified in the issue.\n\n---\n\n## Part 2 — Code Quality Review\n\n### ✅ What's Done Well\n\n- **Defensive coding throughout**: `2>/dev/null || true` on all fallback paths, graceful degradation when fields can't be extracted.\n- **Deliberate design documented**: Exclusion of bare `#N` refs from PR number extraction is commented in-line — the right level of documentation for a non-obvious choice.\n- **Balanced-bracket tasks parser**: Using `python3` for nested-array extraction avoids truncating tasks with nested objects. Correct and future-proof.\n- **Timeout retry preserves partial output**: The check for `.structured_output` from the timed-out first call before triggering a retry is a good optimisation.\n- **Test quality**: Mocking `timeout()` as a bash function is the correct BATS pattern. Tests cover both happy path and the important negative case (bare issue refs must not become PR numbers).\n\n---\n\n### 🔶 Important — Should Fix (follow-up)\n\n**1. Silent ceiling escalation log in implement-task loop**\n\nWhen `base_model` is already `opus`, `_next_model_up \"$base_model\"` returns `\"opus\"`. The log will say `\"escalating to opus\"` when no escalation occurred. Fix:\n\n```bash\nif [[ \"$current_model\" == \"$base_model\" ]]; then\n    log \"Task $task_id retry: already at ceiling model ($base_model), increasing timeout only to ${current_timeout}s\"\nelse\n    log \"Task $task_id retry: escalating to $current_model with timeout ${current_timeout}s\"\nfi\n```\n\n**2. Undeclared `python3` runtime dependency** (`.claude/scripts/implement-issue-orchestrator.sh`)\n\nThe tasks extraction spawns `python3`. Failure is silently swallowed, but the dependency is undeclared. On a minimal CI runner it may not be present. Recommend adding a startup check or documenting it in prerequisites.\n\n---\n\n### 💡 Suggestions — Nice to Have\n\n**3. Missing test for `!N` bang-ref pattern** (`test-stage-runner.bats`)\n\nThe `!N` GitLab MR syntax is implemented but has no test coverage. A simple additional `@test` block exercising `\"Opened MR !17 for review\"` would complete coverage of the `bang_re` path.\n\n**4. Tab/space indentation inconsistency** (`test-stage-runner.bats`)\n\nNew tests in the `FIELD-AWARE STRUCTURED OUTPUT RECOVERY` section use tab indentation while the rest of the file uses 4-space. Recommend normalising to 4-space throughout.","issues":[{"severity":"minor","file":".claude/scripts/implement-issue-orchestrator.sh","line":2420,"description":"When base_model is already at ceiling (opus), _next_model_up returns 'opus' unchanged. The log message 'escalating to opus' is misleading — no escalation occurred. Add a guard to distinguish ceiling-model retries from genuine escalations in the log output."},{"severity":"minor","file":".claude/scripts/implement-issue-orchestrator.sh","line":1008,"description":"python3 is a new implicit runtime dependency introduced by the balanced-bracket tasks parser. It is not validated at startup and its absence silently skips tasks extraction. Either add a startup check or document it in the project prerequisites."},{"severity":"minor","file":".claude/scripts/implement-issue-test/test-stage-runner.bats","line":169,"description":"New tests in the FIELD-AWARE STRUCTURED OUTPUT RECOVERY section use tab indentation while the rest of the file uses 4-space indentation. Normalise to 4-space for consistency."},{"severity":"minor","file":".claude/scripts/implement-issue-test/test-stage-runner.bats","line":169,"description":"The !N GitLab MR bang-ref pattern (bang_re='!([0-9]+)') is implemented in production code but has no test coverage. Add a @test case with result text 'Opened MR !17 for review' to verify extraction."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"2bb247d9-7d6a-4032-8e3b-ed6236f844c9"}
